__NUXT_JSONP__("/php/php-htmlspecialchars-decode-function", {data:[{article:{slug:"php-htmlspecialchars-decode-function",description:"The htmlspecialchars_decode() function converts some predefined HTML entities to characters. \u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E \u003Cstrong\u003EHTML entities that will be decoded are:\u003C\u002Fstrong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n&amp; becomes & (ampersand)\u003Cbr\u003E &quot; becomes \" (double quote)\u003Cbr\u003E &#039; becomes ' (single quote)\u003Cbr\u003E &lt; becomes \u003C (less than)\u003Cbr\u003E &gt; becomes \u003E (greater than)\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe htmlspecialchars_decode() function is the opposite of \u003Ca href='\u002Fphp\u002Fphp-htmlspecialchars-function'\u003Ehtmlspecialchars()\u003C\u002Fa\u003E. ",title:"PHP htmlspecialchars_decode() Function",date:"2021-07-09T13:30:00.000Z",image:"\u002Fimages\u002Fphp\u002Fphp-htmlspecialchars_decode-function.png",tags:["php","htmlspecialchars_decode"],instagram:"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.instagram.com\u002Fp\u002FCRGcPsujIoz\u002F?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link",summery:"The htmlspecialchars() function converts some predefined characters to HTML entities.",toc:[],body:{type:"root",children:[]},dir:"\u002Fphp",path:"\u002Fphp\u002Fphp-htmlspecialchars-decode-function",extension:".md",createdAt:"2023-01-15T15:56:12.367Z",updatedAt:"2023-01-15T15:56:12.368Z"}}],fetch:{},mutations:void 0});